## 1. Purpose

This document defines the recommended color system for OPRMT™ repository documentation, brand assets, diagrams, product materials, website blocks, presentation decks, PDF files, and related visual systems.

The purpose of this file is to keep OPRMT™ visuals consistent, professional, readable, and suitable for public-facing framework documentation.

---

## 2. Brand Color Principle

The OPRMT™ brand should communicate:

```text
structured
technical
trustworthy
professional
controlled
modern
framework-oriented
```

The default visual direction should use dark navy, white, gold, and neutral grays. Accent colors may be used sparingly for calls to action, highlights, status labels, diagrams, and interface elements.

---

## 3. Primary Color Palette

| Color Name | Hex | Recommended Use |
|---|---:|---|
| OPRMT Navy | `#071A2F` | Primary background, headers, footers, hero sections |
| Deep System Blue | `#0B2545` | Secondary background, cards, documentation banners |
| Framework Gold | `#D6A84F` | Accent color, highlights, borders, badges, key terms |
| Clean White | `#FFFFFF` | Main text on dark backgrounds, page background |
| Soft White | `#F7F9FC` | Light section backgrounds, cards, code area background |
