## 8. Accessibility Guidance

When creating public-facing materials:

- Use high contrast between text and background.
- Use white or soft white text on navy backgrounds.
- Avoid gold text on white backgrounds unless the font is large and contrast is verified.
- Avoid red/green-only status communication; include labels.
- Do not rely on color alone to communicate meaning.
- Check buttons and links for readability on mobile devices.
- Keep body text on light backgrounds dark enough for long reading.

Recommended combinations:

| Background | Text |
|---|---|
| `#071A2F` | `#FFFFFF` |
| `#0B2545` | `#F7F9FC` |
| `#FFFFFF` | `#111827` |
| `#F7F9FC` | `#334155` |
| `#D6A84F` | `#071A2F` |

Avoid:

| Background | Text |
|---|---|
| `#FFFFFF` | `#D6A84F` |
| `#F7F9FC` | `#CBD5E1` |
| `#071A2F` | `#334155` |
| `#0B2545` | `#64748B` |

