## 12. Brand Color Restrictions

Do not:

- Use bright neon palettes as the primary OPRMT™ identity.
- Use low-contrast gold text on white backgrounds.
- Use too many accent colors in one asset.
- Replace the primary navy/gold identity with unrelated colors.
- Use playful, cartoon-style palettes for official framework materials.
- Use colors that make OPRMT™ appear casual, unserious, or inconsistent.

